# ECS RTS Project - Coding Standard

When working on this C++ ECS RTS project, always follow these coding standards:

## Naming Conventions
- **Files**: snake_case (e.g., `gameplay_system.cpp`, `unit_factory.hpp`)
- **Classes & Structures**: PascalCase (e.g., `GameplaySystem`, `RenderSystem`)
- **Public Functions**: PascalCase (e.g., `Initialize()`, `Update()`, `GetPosition()`)
- **Private Functions**: camelCase (e.g., `updateInternal()`, `calculateDistance()`)
- **Public Fields**: camelCase (e.g., `position`, `velocity`)
- **Private/Protected Fields**: _camelCase with underscore prefix (e.g., `_playerCount`, `_maxHealth`)

## Formatting
- Use **tabs** for indentation (not spaces)

## When Writing or Modifying Code
- Always apply these conventions consistently
- When creating new files, use snake_case naming
- When creating new classes, functions, or fields, follow the appropriate naming convention
- Maintain tab-based indentation throughout

